To style a button with a bright green background and white text using CSS, you can use the following code snippet. This example assumes you're using a simple HTML button element. The CSS targets the button by its type attribute (`<button>`) and applies the desired styles.

```css
button {
  background-color: #00FF00; /* Bright green background */
  color: white; /* White text */
  padding: 10px 20px; /* Adds some padding inside the button for better clickability */
  border: none; /* Removes the default border */
  border-radius: 5px; /* Rounds the corners of the button */
  cursor: pointer; /* Changes the cursor to a pointer when hovering over the button */
  font-size: 16px; /* Sets the font size for better readability */
  text-align: center; /* Centers the text inside the button */
  display: inline-block; /* Allows for custom padding and margins */
  margin: 10px; /* Adds some space around the button */
}

button:hover {
  background-color: #008000; /* Slightly darker green on hover for visual feedback */
}
```

